entury. novel follows life okonkwo, ibo leader local wrestling champion. exiled upon return, finds community submitted influence western colonisers. realising much life village worsened, hangs himself. "the world end, good among one people abomination others," writes achebe. 100 best english novels. 2005, time magazine listed things fall apart list 100 best english-language novels 1923 2005. things fall apart still one read books modern african literature. novel sold 12 million copies translated 50 languages. book followed sequel, longer ease, originally written second part larger work along arrow god. child cannot pay mother's milk chinua achebe, book things fall apart recognition 30 honorary degrees. acknowledged father modern african literature, chinua awarded 30 honorary degrees universities around world. achebe also many literary awards, inaugural nigerian national merit award 1979 man booker international prize fiction 2007. dorothy lillian gish prize 2010. annual prize given "a man woman made outstanding contribution beauty world mankind’s enjoyment understanding life". praised mandela. south africa's anti-apartheid revolutionary leader nelson mandela called writer "in whose company prison walls fell down". current president south africa jacob zuma described "colossus african writing". literary critics compared achebe's eminence worldwide gabriel garcia marquez, toni morrison handful writers. people & power rob africa function showvideo() { renderpagesvideo('1952572493001', 0, '100%', 473, 'bottomvideo'); $(".article-video-block-img").remove();} source: al jazeera news arts & culture nigeria africa
