chiang mai, thailand - every year northern thailand , groups men gather take part unique activity: beetle fighting. men come fight beetles gamble, others come simply meet socialise friends. fights organised year offer break daily routine small, agrarian villages. participants typically low-income farmers, also wealthy competitors. locals capture rhinoceros beetles jungle beetle mating season september. average beetle sold 50 baht ($1.40), champion-caliber insect go much 3,000 baht ($84). owners bring beetles small arenas fighting takes place. match beetles size character two similar beetles found, bets placed competitors head onto fighting stage - log wood, crafted holes wherein female, pheromone-secreting beetle trapped. two male beetles thus motivated fight female beetle. lift push opponents huge horns; victorious beetle break opponent’s horn cause flee. matches broken rounds time beetles lock horns. match continues 12 rounds, contest declared draw. bets, range 100 baht ($3) much 50,000 baht ($1,400), add drama occasion. losing beetle typically returned jungle, winners kept pieces sugar cane fight again. read more: animal smugglers
