sami al-hajj held without trial afghanistan guantanamo six years [al jazeera] doha, qatar - young boy growing sennar, agricultural sudanese town blue nile, developed keen interest journalism. enthused rich culture history surroundings – sennar capital historic kingdom - began writing school college publications. time go university, left home headed india, spent five years studying political science sociology. always maintained passion media. upon returning sudan, worked father several months, made way united arab emirates. heard new channel set qatar – al jazeera. felt compelled join. eventually taken on, intention would become channel's chechnya correspondent. wife region deep interest it. 9/11 happened everything changed. pakistan october 7, 2001, found pakistan, preparing cross afghanistan cover war al jazeera cameraman. days later, october 11, crossed quetta, pakistan side border. us bombing kabul north country, night also attacking airport kandahar. heading – taliban's power base. kandahar, taliban kept close eye journalists work. would get permission film would accompanied taliban official. one occasion, covertly used small camera made way marketplace – hoping capture uncensored image city residents. caught, arrested detained mosque 12 hours. war continued, crossed back forth afghanistan pakistan. become well known border guards and, african face pakistan, wasn't easily forgotten. came surprise when, december 15, attempted cross back pakistan, stopped. guantanamo files: dozens held innocent remember day clearly. last ramadan. taliban pushed kandahar al jazeera wanted us report life city departure. worried route in, felt relieved arrived border crossing found full journalists. must 70 us, world. wouldn't let cross. knew border guard stopped me. paper, said, directing arrest "sami, al jazeera cameraman". seemed relatively innocuous time; must kind mistake. guard acknowledged journalist. spoke calmly, politely even. intelligence officer came. read more: growing guantanamo one point, gave option taking passport heading back islamabad. job do, felt sure would resolved soon. spent night border guard's office. next day, telephoned intelligence officer. either come take him, i'll let go, heard say. thirty minutes later, intelligence officer arrived. taken office arrested. flight felt like something horror film. beaten randomly. time landed, feet numb cold, bodies frozen stiff. sami al-hajj still, strangely amicable. treated well. case mistaken identity, assured me. waiting released. free move around office allowed call family. even brought doctor see cold grew worse. hours turned days – would spend 23 total. time, i'd listen news small radio. one day, report incident involving arab prisoner; attacked pakistani guards bus escaped. that, noticed armed guard outside room. bagram then, one night, moved. taken airport group arabs. around 25 30 us. handed american soldiers. bags placed heads handcuffed human chain. loaded military cargo plane. flight felt like something horror film. beaten randomly. time landed, feet numb cold, bodies frozen stiff. rolled plane runway. twisted ankle fell. bagram airbase american custody. soldiers hyped up, angry; sort aggression could come extreme fear. strip searched us asked fighting america. truly seemed believe enemies kind holy war. began question osama bin laden. thought i'd interviewed report broadcast al jazeera weeks earlier. wanted know knew whereabouts. course, mistaken. never met interviewed bin laden. questioning revealed that, even case mistaken identity, doubt fact journalist. guantanamo remembered: personal perspective looking back it, believe pakistanis handed fully aware wasn't "sami" americans looking for. playing game. simply got caught bid convince americans cooperating – strongly doubt one. bagram brutal. held hangar, 20 prisoners cage. weren't allowed move, talk, stand look one another. wondered prisoners wished could know stories. even listened conversations soldiers, hoping glean kind insight lives. seemed young. would take pictures posed, rambo-style, front us flag. interrogated bagram, air intimidation ever-present. noise constant – dogs barking, planes landing taking off, guns fired, people screaming. couldn't understand treating us like this. wasn't america knew films i'd seen. kept getting flashbacks movies, trying reconcile taking place around me. reminded would least make interesting story, ever able write it. kandahar 17 days bagram, transferred kandahar. conditions better there. stayed tents – 15 prisoners each. psychological torture continued. would make us watch dropped koran toilet buckets; would try make us feel uncomfortable way could. remember overhearing soldier say: "let's torture them, wanted kill us." questioned al jazeera. acknowledged wasn't person looking for. still wasn't released. every month, sent 40 prisoners somewhere else. first, didn't know "somewhere" was. gradually came learn place called guantanamo. five months, among last group prisoners kandahar sent there. guantanamo flight took day so, hard tell exactly long. went first turkey, switched planes american airbase. flew cargo plane, seated log soldiers standing behind us. wore headphones goggles mouths covered entire time. eating going toilet. back kandahar, people learned transported, would stop eating drinking day before. still people wet journey. landed guantanamo, taken one one medical check-up fingerprints photograph taken. sent straight interrogation. three people questioned – one cia, one fbi another military intelligence. lasted three hours. process breaking us began immediately. never stopped. sleep deprivation key component psychological torture. prevented sleeping seven consecutive days. time, one round interrogations, male soldier female soldier intercourse front me. things happened, would go somewhere else mind – memorising koran calculating prayer times. soldiers colour treated us humanely others. remember one, particular, explained follow orders. sami al-hajj prisoners lost it. could see happening. one stood spot days. others would shout out. "let god come save you," soldiers would sneer. many restrictions. weren't allowed talk stand cells. allowed take shower week did, forced walk naked cell shower. soldiers colour treated us humanely others. remember one, particular, explained follow orders. became clear weren't going released conditions weren't going improve, us embarked hunger strike. european prisoners suggested way negotiating. became form protest. already hungry wasn't hard do, especially realised freedom precious food. would drink water, wouldn't eat anything. way resisting. but, 30 days hunger strike, force-feeding would begin. hard convey traumatic is. became form torture itself. would tie us hands legs force tube nose. time, fluid would enter lungs. we'd coughing choking lungs filled liquid. often, they'd over-feed us vomited. even threw up, they'd keep going. vomit would dry faces bodies. weren't allowed clean away smell became unbearable. they'd use tube multiple prisoners without cleaning it. sami's colleagues held regular events mark detention guantanamo ensure forgotten [al jazeera] began longest hunger strike 2007. lasted 480 days ended time guantanamo over. kept telling i'd released immediately stopped it. wanted know would never collaborate them. i'd told many times i'd freed, reason believe now. african american soldiers showed press coverage hunger strike, inspired keep going. could see impact. would eat guantanamo, vowed. campaign already started haissa manna secure release many behind-the-scenes efforts taking place. then, finally, 2008, lawyer, clive stafford smith, told freed, along eight others. arrived sudanese capital, khartoum, may 1, 2008. sami taken hospital khartoum immediately return sudan [al jazeera] guantanamo time guantanamo, met around 90 percent inmates there. tell none met ever threat us. young men – afghan farmers uighur refugees escaping persecution china; othe