2015-16 el nino event major phenomenon, affecting weather worldwide. one swing slow pendulum called el nino southern oscillation (enso). natural system whereby warm water equatorial pacific appears slosh west east back again. side pendulum swing called la nina, female child, spanish. boy opposite girl, la nina produces many opposite weather effects el nino. expect la nina last, approximately 75 percent probability, least april 2018. brings strong upwelling cold, nutrient-rich water along peruvian coast, boosting fish catch. periodic failure industry first alerted us alternative swings el nino (fishing collapse) la nina (abundant catch). importantly, moving warm water one side pacific moves weather patterns whole world. major areas uplift transposed west, taking heaviest rain them. effects elsewhere world current la nina notably dramatic: next four months, likely be: much wetter normal in: much drier normal in: northern australia us gulf coast indonesia malaysia southeastern africa northern brazil may well colder, yet drier normal alaska western canada, cold often penetrating northern great plains western us. variations weather might otherwise expected, northern winter, may caused la nina. however, one influence atmosphere. warming world produces equally dramatic changes - loss complete ice cover arctic ocean, winter, likely influence la nina europe winter. reading: http://www.cpc.ncep.noaa.gov/products/precip/cwlink/mjo/enso.shtml source: al jazeera weather africa europe asia pacific us & canada
